As much as native Pittsburghers
like to see themselves as munch-
ing Primanti’s on an I-beam, the
sobering reality is that most are
probably wearing scrubs or sitting
in lecture halls. Sure, Pittsburgh
still has a vibrant and admirable
blue-collar demographic, but it’s
no longer a majority presence.

So, why do we still cling to pro-
letariat holdovers like rioting? It’s

all part of the narrative. Whereas‘

some cities have distinguishing
landmarks or unrivaled artistic
offerings, Pittsburgh —— for all

its beauty and success in the aca-
demic and medical ﬁelds —— sets
itself apart by being the little in-

dustrial town that could. “Yeah, I

Pittsburgh. That city where folks
are tough as nails, living out the
spirit of ol’ Joe Magarac. But, boy,
you should see what they are do-
ing with hospitals.”

To make sure we do not lose
our workrnan’s credentials, we li-
onize rough—and-tumble behavior.

Rioting just happens to fall in the _

serendipitous halfway point be-
tween blue—collar toughness and
collegiate merriment. Through the
Darwinian bestiality of rioting we
can continually reinvent ourselves
as a city where only the strong sur-
vive, even if, by all other accounts,

i we are a pre-eminently livable city.

Fortunately for rioting, there
is an element of fun to our public
displays. ’

In riots, Pittsburgh appears
as the best of two worlds: hard
as steel but brimming over with
amusement.

_Some might worry that this
whole charade stiﬂes progress.
By rnirning an antique spirit, we
stymie the growth of a new Pitts-
burgh.

How can we ever scramble to
the top of magazine rankings if
we suffer the stigma of a sooty,
raucous city?

Such fears are unfounded. Like
any kitsch, Pittsburgh’s throw-
back, blue-collar spirit is far more
decorative than it is deﬁnitive, and,
therefore, thoroughly benign.

Furthermore, talk of “authen-
tic” culture is almost always mis-
guided and rhetorical.

Culture is largely an affected
behavior: the product of how a
community views itself and how
they are unfairly stereotyped. “Real
culture” is just a buzz-phrase by
way of which an individual .can
elevate the aspects of a culture he
enjoys.

Therefore, carry on my friends.
Be the riot you wish to see and sa-
vor the beautiful disorder of it all.

